  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>white long grain rice </strong>to a pot with a lid with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and 175ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml]<strong> </span>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1066Step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1066Step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1066Step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1066Step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1066Step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, add a handful of <strong>flour</strong> to a plate</p><p>Crack the<strong> egg<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into a shallow bowl and beat with a fork</p><p>Add the<strong> panko breadcrumbs</strong> to another plate</p><p>Coat the <strong>basa fillets</strong> in the <strong>flour</strong>, tap off the excess, then add them into the <strong>beaten egg</strong> and finally press them into the <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong> firmly to evenly coat all over</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1066Step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1066Step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1066Step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1066Step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1066Step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a pot over a low heat</p><p>Add the <strong>tomato ketchup</strong>, <strong>soy sauce</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until thick and sticky, then remove from the heat and set aside for serving – this is your <strong>amai sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1066Step-3-x200.jpg",
